<emphasis id="DC2C0D577F3012FFFA816180ED027DAF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf. Type Protologue: [Algeria] &quot;Barbarie, dans les 
<normalizedToken id="7E4A2AD783EA141B9F1DE7558AE232C8" originalValue="prés">pres</normalizedToken>
, aux environs de Lacalle&quot;.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB5453F18F6EF05A0558DAEA79487D6F" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="4982C88ACAB6100AEC2BB15FD640BC6C" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="237C5BBBE1B42AF6C1CC37C3399AE3F5" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
Currently, the species 
<taxonomicName id="98C6FEE96F5C08B02736EB0861316C1A" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="097DCB6FB3270B095F3298FFCA4CF251" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. has at least two synonyms: 
<taxonomicName id="A28EED24417613471A17DE133507FF34" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuroides" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" rank="species" species="alopecuroides">
<emphasis id="E6B90E15CB78F70033CCA3FAA72BCC2B" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">B. alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. and 
<taxonomicName id="60A1D37F66040230FBBCA64EE8DEEC87" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="7C487F006B06612E61339FB45FD5B36C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41EE17CA23CDFABFEC7F453CFCCEF723" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
In describing 
<taxonomicName id="69EA36033F400F43C99083305ACC6E19" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="C24402F0610C65A49EC94BF4968D8F7B" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EA034130504438C73B172285839E25FB" author="Poiret, JLM" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B24" refString="Poiret, JLM, 1789. Voyage en Barbarie: ou lettres ecrites de l'ancienne Numidie pendant les annees 1785 &amp; 1786, sur la religion, les coutumes &amp; les moeurs des Maures &amp; des Arabes-Bedouins: avec un essai sur l'histoire naturelle de ce pays. JBF de la Rochelle, Paris.https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13598" title="Voyage en Barbarie: ou lettres ecrites de l'ancienne Numidie pendant les annees 1785 &amp; 1786, sur la religion, les coutumes &amp; les moeurs des Maures &amp; des Arabes-Bedouins: avec un essai sur l'histoire naturelle de ce pays. JBF de la Rochelle, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13598" year="1789">Poiret (1789</bibRefCitation>
: 100) stated in the protologue diagnosis &quot;Panicula conferta erecta, spiculis oblongis subsessilibus, aristis inferne spiraliter contortis.&quot; followed by a description in French and the locotypic indication indicating this species grows around La Calle [now El Kala, El Tarf province, Algeria].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35CDD6885592DADE864FCC3DEDAB1EC7" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
During our search for original material in the herbaria conserving the plants of Poiret (FI, H, P and UPS), we found only one specimen collected by him. There is a sheet in P (P02622864) from Numidia (Algeria 
<normalizedToken id="77B424DE1F83D118316EA955262BA75B" originalValue="“Numidia”">&quot;Numidia&quot;</normalizedToken>
included in the full title of his publication), registered as original material, bearing a single plant annotated as 
<taxonomicName id="598DE9F027586B041C7A49F7C660D476" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="7FDA2AC66A140C4C584F66255B58CCC3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with five labels transcribed below; one of them handwritten by Poiret:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B6BEA1134327BABDCE5F76D7987FD404" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Label 1: [printed]. Herb. Poiret in Herb. Moquin-Tandom.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF9938982EE1CD992C787FA3BA9492ED" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
Label 2: [handwritten by Poiret] &quot;brom. contortus Desf. 
<taxonomicName id="1D5867DA47BF0F8E7BB2229A547E1105" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="5214051EBC06718EB873BB07CBE77633" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(n) Panicula conferta erecta spiculis oblongis subsessilibus, aristis inferne spiraliter contortis. (nobis) h. Poiret ex Numidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E2A5ACB4EDD88FA3E1088C7FB8ED0882" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Label 3: [printed]: barcode Herbier museum Paris P 02622864</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E437AC522936EA6D845EC41B0A567A6A" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
Label 4: [handwritten] 
<taxonomicName id="C698370A9F90FE6A8ECB37510F673696" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="99633ECD8CEF6EBDBE94CA910A9B222C" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poiret, Det. P. Smith 3/72
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="519DFADBB422E471A3242F082F9CD72D" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Label 5: [printed]. Herb. Mus. Paris</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBB9E5D604D5E3F9A3681CCB6BD890B4" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
As this specimen bears a label handwritten by Poiret with his description of 
<taxonomicName id="BF1F8B812D089D5BAF2E5D0F24659E1C" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="EFFC2AE02D403887AD00E7DB3E8299F8" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the word 
<normalizedToken id="BFEED4F30094E15EDC4F42976749970C" originalValue="“nobis”">&quot;nobis&quot;</normalizedToken>
[our], indicating the author is describing a new species, it seems sure that it is original material and it is suitable to be described as a lectotype. In addition, there is no other specimen matching with 
<taxonomicName id="DFB69940D2F8386E66C461DFD738C448" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="1786B42F2E6A396910AAA175DE98E2EA" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. in FI (Chiara Nepi pers. comm. 2018); nor in H (Raino Lampinen pers. comm. 1994; Henry 
<normalizedToken id="0A1418C9D40AD6B6FCDA386C1A26BC68" originalValue="Väre">Vaere</normalizedToken>
pers. comm. 2018) nor in UPS (Dr. Mats Hjertson pers. comm. 2018).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B62D506C589C0CB0331A89D08BC340DF" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">
When 
<bibRefCitation id="59E6C3F356FEFED6B23BAF98AED58B7C" author="Desfontaines, RL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B7" refString="Desfontaines, RL, 1798. Flora Atlantica (1st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.323" title="Flora Atlantica (1 st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 323" year="1798">Desfontaines (1798</bibRefCitation>
: 95), describes 
<taxonomicName id="A5D835FD0B8924C79A3D636309A22579" authorityName="Desf" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus contortus" order="Poales" pageId="1" pageNumber="54" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="2AC2D3121C6DD50F178D5B05CE6BFAE5" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="54">Bromus contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, his description closely matches that of 
<bibRefCitation id="618847B89FCFD5016F590BA6CEAF7944" author="Poiret, JLM" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B24" refString="Poiret, JLM, 1789. Voyage en Barbarie: ou lettres ecrites de l'ancienne Numidie pendant les annees 1785 &amp; 1786, sur la religion, les coutumes &amp; les moeurs des Maures &amp; des Arabes-Bedouins: avec un essai sur l'histoire naturelle de ce pays. JBF de la Rochelle, Paris.https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.13598" title="Voyage en Barbarie: ou lettres ecrites de l'ancienne Numidie pendant les annees 1785 &amp; 1786, sur la religion, les coutumes &amp; les moeurs des Maures &amp; des Arabes-Bedouins: avec un essai sur l'histoire naturelle de ce pays. JBF de la Rochelle, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 13598" year="1789">Poiret (1789)</bibRefCitation>
. In his diagnosis, Desfontaines adds that the spikelets are &quot;quindecimfloribus, 
<normalizedToken id="0540C1DCDC5C92AEFCC57B0314DF9B7D" originalValue="…pubescentibus”">...pubescentibus&quot;</normalizedToken>
. At the end, he has doubts about his plant and 
<pageBreakToken id="A9CC66B66C30102A4B325B74751C73BB" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" start="start">transcribes</pageBreakToken>
a reference to the description of Poiret &quot;An Bromus alopecuros? Poiret. Itin. 2. P. 100)&quot;. Subsequently, he includes a more detailed description and asserts &quot;Habitat prope La Calle&quot;. The only known original material for 
<taxonomicName id="3C21B9490230D4B6508764BA5B8E3F9F" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="611E6AE4B63B052D1250D79C46FEF37A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the illustration quoted in 
<bibRefCitation id="3FC4D9A8BB7BDDF629D4E19BD7B23390" author="Desfontaines, RL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B7" refString="Desfontaines, RL, 1798. Flora Atlantica (1st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.323" title="Flora Atlantica (1 st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 323" year="1798">Desfontaines (1798</bibRefCitation>
: plate 25) and a single sheet in P (MNHN-P P00320328) bearing two specimens mounted on it with a printed label: 
<emphasis id="9A701E0EA78BFBAD2C008500BEE510B2" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Herbier de la FLORE ATANTIQUE 
<normalizedToken id="09215027E48559C5207E7BFC8DCDB4C4" originalValue="donné">donne</normalizedToken>
au Museum par M. DESFONTAINES
</emphasis>
and annotated &quot; 
<emphasis id="2970121DF3EE020A7AA3B37A9559E52C" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus contortus</emphasis>
&quot; handwritten (unknown by whom). There is another label, handwritten by Desfontaines, containing the exact diagnosis and description as it appears in Flora Atlantica (
<bibRefCitation id="0C74AA61922041974043151E84E0A8DE" author="Desfontaines, RL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B7" refString="Desfontaines, RL, 1798. Flora Atlantica (1st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.323" title="Flora Atlantica (1 st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 323" year="1798">Desfontaines 1798</bibRefCitation>
: 95). Maybe Desfontaines is surprised one specimen is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="EEDACC7D96507B22ECBF136B09830EB6" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="9B6C02E7250D1F443D4BF9BA88252351" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but not the other one, justifying his doubt in the description where he states &quot;perhaps 
<emphasis id="5CC0C1E11A3D412AE99FF0675B295B2D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
?&quot; This sheet bears two plants. The one on the left seems to be 
<taxonomicName id="CDDB4CCA0CC121B880C4258F9B7688EC" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus lanceolatus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanceolatus">
<emphasis id="4A21D4479723D7A65DD1ECF9E707D181" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Roth and the one on the right is a fragment (contracted and erect panicle with subsessile spikelets) of a specimen matching 
<taxonomicName id="8A56AC03F4F4EA9183C00BEBB447F9A1" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="603D672B32AC3BA06727D3720C37128B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf., that also exemplifies the typical resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="217574559E18F606A722B5CEE0993EE0" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="0B631EFA2CE86AF8D2652B2020329E79" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. Therefore, the sheet in question does not represent a specimen as defined in the 
<emphasis id="AC3DC1C4ED4058EAD9B57BF2CF5D0EB3" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Code</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="261CD6515F9484168855A150D9CA85DB" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Botany, British and Foreign" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B33" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
); but each of the two plants on the sheet is a specimen in its own right. Only one specimen is original material for 
<taxonomicName id="9A95A2DE3EE19C31F7228B29ED3EF6FE" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="1A4C201AD11A7282A6F4F7219A02B11B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf. It is possible that the illustration in 
<bibRefCitation id="73BD23D9F27B314886853B333769F286" author="Desfontaines, RL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B7" refString="Desfontaines, RL, 1798. Flora Atlantica (1st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.323" title="Flora Atlantica (1 st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 323" year="1798">Desfontaines (1798</bibRefCitation>
: plate 25) was drawn from the plant designated here as lectotype.
</paragraph>
<caption id="584DE0ABE400E4E863A438A58C96FDFE" ID-Zenodo-Dep="2702115" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.119.30254.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/297548" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="3E969EDDFA3825FD6D3F9C8677595918" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="65BD590DAF072B0BEC45F2CE4A728CDC" bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="7990F61ACE655F17A3B07EA1D2BEA12A" authorityName="Poir., Voy. Barbarie. 2: 100 - 101" authorityYear="1789" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="CCA9F86E142563EE02DBEE26E7CAF09B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: It is a complete specimen preserved at the MNHN Collection Vascular plants Specimen with barcode P02622864. (Available at http://coldb.mnhn.fr/catalognumber/mnhn/p/p02622864).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="BF8E75412E6B7A64FC94529097E0EADD" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Choosing the specimen on the right of the sheet MNHN-P P00320328 (Figure 2) as lectotype, which taxonomically matches 
<taxonomicName id="E69C2ABA7289BFDE9E2F3B94D39BE31B" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="F4FAA0E8766B5EC7031584A10ECE2475" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir., the name becomes a taxonomic or heterotypic synonym (
<bibRefCitation id="BB3FFA6B88289716877DF09E0274D47F" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Botany, British and Foreign" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B33" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) of it, as 
<bibRefCitation id="58735B53BEB6B4BF8B1727CD8FB5DAB3" author="Persoon, CH" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B23" refString="Persoon, CH, 1805. Synopsis plantarum, seu enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum. Pars prima. Carol. Frid. Cramerum, Parisii Lutetiorum. http://bibdigital.rjb.csic.es/spa/FichaLibro.php?Libro=383" title="Synopsis plantarum, seu enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum. Pars prima. Carol. Frid. Cramerum, Parisii Lutetiorum. http: // bibdigital. rjb. csic. es / spa / FichaLibro. php? Libro = 383" year="1805">Persoon (1805</bibRefCitation>
, 1: 95) asserted. Moreover, it is also possible that the heterogeneous material in this sheet is the origin of some misidentifications of 
<taxonomicName id="C14648ADE25DAA15FF60F900F1164D73" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. lanceolatus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="lanceolatus">
<emphasis id="35AF732A80AC143735CB37B3514AFBB8" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. lanceolatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Roth as 
<taxonomicName id="5602FCC5002DCCB70550A3A171CE405F" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="54D5C12CC63C223848201B922C94048A" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf.
</paragraph>
<caption id="91D883AF121DDDE461FFD034D4A484A8" ID-Zenodo-Dep="2702117" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.119.30254.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/297549" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="2BBBB1AFB5B63A25818B5EAA26F821F8" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="440A169565828F113483AE4D0F95B1ED" bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="A2DC35B1DC380B88D45EFCF9937E0528" authorityName="Desf" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="E14B00B80B7BC24E396E98226D239E86" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf. is the specimen on the right having subsessile spikelets conserved in the MNHN Collection Vascular plants with barcode P00320328 (image available at: https://science.mnhn.fr/institution/mnhn/collection/p/item/p00320328?listIndex=1&amp;listCount=4).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="A9D4D2AFF1E39F099488A80B08D7F6FE" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">
Later, 
<bibRefCitation id="2C128DF90BAF71206429E6E139702104" author="Poiret, JLM" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="10" pageNumber="63" refId="B25" refString="Poiret, JLM, 1810. Encyclopedie Methodique. Botanique. Supplement, Tome I. H Agasse, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.826" title="Encyclopedie Methodique. Botanique. Supplement, Tome I. H Agasse, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 826" year="1810">Poiret (1810</bibRefCitation>
: 703) describes 
<taxonomicName id="405FE2A3844B40A2DD8819268552C4F4" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus alopecuroides" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alopecuroides">
<emphasis id="2F633C5A77E1B686D8A2459A7F57BCBE" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus alopecuroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; 
<emphasis id="E813E9F8D7326A1646AABA921C5ECADE" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus</emphasis>
panicula conferta, erecta; spiculis oblongis, pubescentibus, quindecimfloris, subsessilibus; aristis 
<normalizedToken id="0851933D08E769ABF3D9243255461BD1" originalValue="infernè">inferne</normalizedToken>
spiraliter contortis&quot;. This description is almost identical to the former of 
<taxonomicName id="B9A53AF23897B4ADE853F7F8E9C2BFF9" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="36FEB4E241D5C646D062ED5C9A1ED2CD" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its only difference is to include &quot;pubescentibus, quindecimfloris&quot;, the same features 
<bibRefCitation id="A8533AD838D88EE5D780E178558FA32F" author="Desfontaines, RL" journalOrPublisher="Archives de la Flore de France et d'Allemagne" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="B7" refString="Desfontaines, RL, 1798. Flora Atlantica (1st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.323" title="Flora Atlantica (1 st ed). C Panckoucke, Paris. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 323" year="1798">Desfontaines (1798</bibRefCitation>
: 95) uses to describe 
<taxonomicName id="DF5E905EF4BE05A8A211D337D256D8D1" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="84A186A094F1C75C9CCC204A331B8B7B" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Poiret continues adding the references to 
<taxonomicName id="8C3A0B733FEB3A4AC976DFA50EBEAFF1" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. alopecuros" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="alopecuros">
<emphasis id="7BA54D8A1B7FBB7B9C4CC3A2E4073BB1" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. alopecuros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. and the synonym 
<taxonomicName id="C41706F3A5C65AB8FF25C60D81C4A9F4" family="Poaceae" genus="B." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="B. contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="1E185FFEC88868C619716929A197D837" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">B. contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desf. Therefore, this name does not need a Lectoype as it is a superfluous and illegitimate renaming (Art. 52. 1) of 
<taxonomicName id="B20990956894A47D6B5678BB5546F813" authorityName="Desf" authorityYear="1798" class="Liliopsida" family="Gramineae" genus="Bromus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bromus contortus" order="Poales" pageId="2" pageNumber="55" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="contortus">
<emphasis id="8C27FD3727839013362F7BDDA3FF3B38" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="55">Bromus contortus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Poir. and has the same type we select here for that name.
</paragraph>
